ENG

You have written a clean and nice code.

The menu part is not in a loop, so the program keeps closing repeatedly. I think you might have overlooked it.

I experienced some issues when opening files because you added the directory while opening, which caused problems when running. Writing "books.txt" directly would allow others to run the project without issues.

Since the writing to the file is not done properly, if I add books to the system and exit without deleting anything, it doesn't write the added books to the file.

Additionally, you have skipped specifying how some files should be opened. It directly opens in read mode, but it would be better to mention it explicitly every time.

You can prevent some possible issues by adding a try-except logic.

For instance, when trying to get numerical values for release date and page number and not receiving them, there is incorrect data entry; you can handle it with a try-except block. Reference: Python Try Except.
